EFF leader Julius Malema led a march through the streets of Johannesburg to the power utility's head office, Megawatt Park. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Economic Freedom Fighters has marched to Eskom's Megawatt Park in Johannesburg against load-shedding and the privatisation of the power utility.
The march comes just a day after Soweto residents protested against Eskom demanding a flat rate of R150 for electricity. READ: EFF takes aim at Ramaphosa's Sona EFF leader Julius Malema says President Cyril Ramaphosa and Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan are to blame for continued power cuts.